# Content Format Standards

## File Format (Jupytext)

- Source files are Markdown (`.md`) - these are version controlled
- Jupytext converts `.md` → `.ipynb` notebooks (gitignored)
- Students run `uv run python generate_notebooks.py` to generate notebooks
- Use fenced code blocks with language tags (```python, ```sql, ```bash) - each becomes a notebook cell
- Structure: concept explanation → code example → exercise

## Code Block Rules

- Every ```python block becomes an executable cell
- Mark expected outputs with `# Result:` comments
- Code must be runnable in sequence from top to bottom
- Use SQLite and standard library when possible (zero-install)

## Reproducibility

- All examples must run on Windows, macOS, Linux
- Prefer SQLite over external databases
- Embed sample data in code or provide seed scripts
- Use Docker only when topic requires it (PostgreSQL features, distributed systems)
